In this example, this task will consume one instance of Answer. However, two instances will be produced, since ColAgent1 and ColAgent2 will produce each one an instance, what makes two instances to process. To process both at the same time, set the cardinality of the WFConsumes cardinality to 1..*

There is at least one collaborator. The interaction declares there can be many collaborators by indicating a cardinality of 1..*. If nothing else is specified, the interaction will be concreted with all existing agents playing the role Collaborator.

In such interaction, a message delivered to the agent playing that role will trigger as many messages as collaborators are involved. In this case, copies of the same instance of Request is delivered to all Collaborators.

Response messages will be gathered by the initiator as separated messages. The initiator will receive N instances of an Answer element. The initiator can define tasks capable of processing all N instances at the same time or one by one (without any predefined order)

A task declares with gtcreates that an instance of an interaction of type SampleInteraction has to be created. Instances of an interaction are known as conversations. The task can determine which agents will participate or let the system find proper participants. The later is the default action.

Other tasks, like ProcessingTheRequest, gain access to the interaction by linking themselves to the interaction type with IAccesses. A task can be triggered using information from the mental state or from the ongoing conversations. Conversation contain the pieces of information interchanged among agents. Nevertheless, this information is accesible only if the task definition states the task has access to instances of the coversation type, the interaction.

This role extends the colaborator role. The generalization relationship impliesthat the agent playing the specialized role gains as well the skills associated to the generalized role. Tasks associated to more specialized roles are scheduled before tasks associated to their generalizing roles; hence, they can be executed before and this execution, if tasks share the same kind of input preconditions, means aborting the corresponding tasks of parent roles. This permits to customize the behavior provided by a role in an interaction or in other circumstances.
